Who is General William McCasland?

General William Neil "Neil" McCasland is a retired U.S. Air Force Major General. He has been missing since February 27, 2026, from his home in Albuquerque, New Mexico. 

His official Air Force biography and other records confirm key elements of his expertise: 

Education: U.S. Air Force Academy (B.S. in astronautical engineering); MIT (PhD in astronautical engineering under a Hertz Foundation fellowship); Harvard Kennedy School.

Key Roles:
Chief engineer on the Department of Defense’s Global Positioning System (GPS) program.
System Program Director, Space Based Laser Project Office (Los Angeles AFB, ~2000–2001).
Various leadership positions with the National Reconnaissance Office (NRO) and space research/acquisition.
Director of Special Programs, Office of the Under Secretary of Defense for Acquisition, Technology and Logistics (Pentagon, 2009–2011). This involved oversight of highly classified Special Access Programs (SAPs).
Commander of the Air Force Research Laboratory (AFRL) at Wright-Patterson AFB, Ohio (a site long tied to advanced aerospace research and UFO lore in popular speculation).
Other commands included the Phillips Research Site at Kirtland AFB, New Mexico.

These positions placed him at the center of advanced space systems, directed energy weapons, and black-budget programs. The Director of Special Programs role, in particular, involved executive secretary duties for the Special Access Program Oversight Committee—giving broad visibility into the most sensitive classified efforts (often described in media as covering a large share of DoD’s most restricted "black" projects). 

Post-retirement (2013), he worked in technology roles, including as director of technology at Applied Technology Associates, a defense contractor involved in advanced projects. 

The Disappearance:
On February 27, 2026, McCasland (then 68) left his Albuquerque home on foot around 10–11 a.m. while his wife was out. He did not take his phone, prescription glasses, or wearable devices. 

A Silver Alert was issued. Searches (including by New Mexico Search and Rescue) have continued in areas like the Sandia Mountains, with some clothing items recovered but no sign of him as of mid-2026.
He reportedly mentioned "brain fog" or mental fog and was trying to step down from at least one role shortly before vanishing. His wife has described him as sharp, an avid hiker/outdoorsman, and not suffering from dementia or similar issues. 

Authorities (Bernalillo County Sheriff’s Office, with FBI assistance) have found no clear evidence of foul play, though his wallet, revolver, and other items remain unaccounted for. Speculation persists due to his background. 

UFO / Reverse Engineering Connections:
His career at Wright-Patterson (linked in lore to Roswell materials and advanced tech analysis) and oversight of SAPs have fueled heavy speculation in UFO/UAP communities. Some journalists (e.g., Ross Coulthart) have called the disappearance a potential "national security crisis" because of the sensitive knowledge he held. 

He had documented 2016 interactions (via leaked Podesta emails) with figures interested in UAP disclosure, including Tom DeLonge and others discussing non-human intelligence topics. His wife has publicly pushed back, stating he has "no special knowledge" about ET/Roswell/UFOs and that any such associations were brief/limited. 

No public, declassified evidence directly ties him to active UFO reverse-engineering programs. His work focused on mainstream (though highly classified) DoD science and technology—lasers, space systems, photonics, etc. Claims of him overseeing "UFO reverse engineering" remain speculative and unproven.

The case remains open and unsolved. Searches have been hampered by terrain and weather. Official statements emphasize it as a missing person investigation without confirmed ties to his past work. The high-profile background has understandably generated conspiracy theories, but concrete evidence for foul play, abduction, or silencing is lacking so far.

